['SUMMARY: RECOMMENDATIONS BEING FRAMED BY KUWAIT PLANNING BOARD WHICH WOULD CREATE CATEGORY OF "PERMANENT RESIDENTS".

THIS SYSTEM, IT IS HOPED, WOULD ALLOW COUNTRY TO RETAIN VALUED EXPATRIATE WORKERS WITHOUT DILUTING DEMOGRAPHIC COM- POSITION OF COUNTRY'S CITIZENS OR FURTHER TAXING AN ALREADY OVERBURDENED GOVERNMENT WELFARE SYSTEM OF QUALITY EDUCATION, HOUSING, ETC.
TO ITS CITIZENS.

UNDER THIS SYSTEM, IF ADOPTED, "PERMANENT RESIDENTS" WOULD CHIEFLY ENJOY INCREASED ECONOMIC OPPORTUNITIES (E.G. OWN REAL ESTATE) AND SECURITY FROM ARBITRARY DEPORTATION WITHOUT NECESSARILY BEING GRANTED GREATER POLITICAL RIGHTS OR WELFARE BENEFITS.
IT ALSO LIKELY GOK WILL BE URGED TO MORE CLOSELY COORDINATE ITS MANPOWER POLICIES WITH OTHER ARAB GULF STATES IN ORDER TO AVOID FURTHER UNRESTRICTED COMPETITION FOR SKILLED PROFESSIONALS AND WORKERS.
END SUMMARY.

IN VISIT WITH KEY KUWAIT PLANNING BOARD STAFF MEMBER FOR MANPOWER QUESTIONS, EMBOFF WAS GIVEN SOME INSIGHTS INTO BOARD'S LIKELY RECOMMENDATIONS TO GOK RE LIBERALIZING RIGHTS AND BENEFITS FOR LARGE EXPATRIATE COMMUNITY RESIDING IN KUWAIT.
STAFF MEMBER, WHO ONE OF PRINCIPALS ON COMMITTEE CHARGED WITH STUDYING ENTIRE QUESTION FOR GOK, TOLD EMBOFF THAT IN 1973 MORE PEOPLE LEFT KUWAIT THAN ENTERED FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MANY YEARS.

THIS COUPLED WITH INCREASING BOOM IN THE ENTIRE AREA AND A CONCOMITANT QUICKENING OF COMPETITION FOR SKILLED WORKERS AND PROFESSIONALS HAS FORCED GOK TO RE- EXAMINE ITS CITIZENSHIP POLICIES AND TO CONSIDER TAKING STRONGER MEASURES TO KEEP AND ATTRACT SUCH INDIVIDUALS (FOR THOROUGH DISCUSSION OF QUESTION SEE REFAIR).

SOLUTIONS PREVIOUSLY FLOATED TO SOLVE PROBLEM HAVE INCLUDED A RADICAL LIBERALIZATION IN THE GRANTING OF CITIZENSHIP AND CREATION OF A CATERGORY OF "PERMANENT RESIDENTS" TO AVOID VIOLATION OF ARAB LEAGUE STRICTURES AGAINST LIQUIDATING PALESTINIAN QUESTION.
WHILE FINAL PLANNING BOARD POSITION HAS NOT BEEN FORMULATED, IT NOW APPEARS THINKING HOW TO DEAL WITH PROBLEM HAS BEGUN TO CRYSTALLIZE.
THE PLANNING BOARD STAFF WILL LIKELY RECOMMEND AGAINST ANY RADICAL LIBERALIZATION IN GRANTING KUWAITI CITIZEN- SHIP.
THIS COMES NOT ONLY BECAUSE SUCH A MOVE WOULD RADICALLY ALTER THE DEMOGRAPHIC AND SOCIAL CHARACTER OF THE STATE
BUT ALSO BECAUSE AT PRESENT KUWAITI CITIZENSHIP CONFERS UPON ITS RECIPIENTS A HOST OF PRIVILEGES WITHOUT REQUIRING MANY RECIPROCAL OBLIGATIONS.
THUS, KUWAITIS ARE ENTITLED TO HOUSING, HEALTH CARE, EDUCATION, JOB SECURITY, ETC., BUT DO NOT PAY TAXES AND ARE NOT SUBJECT TO CONSCRIPTION.

WHILE STAFF MEMBER AVOIDED SAYING SO DIRECTLY, THIS HAS CREATED A SITUATION WHERE INDIVIDUAL INCENTIVES HAVE LARGELY BEEN KILLED, FORCING KUWAIT TO RELY HEAVILY UPON ITS EXPATRIATE POPULATION TO MAKE THE WHOLE SYSTEM WORK.
MOREOVER, THE GOK IS PRESENTLY HARD- PRESSED TO KEEP ITS PROMISES TO ITS CITIZENS IN SUCH AREAS AS HOUSING, HEALTH CARE, AND EDUCATION DESPITE ITS EMBARRASSING RICHES.
THE IMPLICATION OF THIS IS CLEAR.
IF KUWAIT GRANTS MANY ADDITIONAL PEOPLE CITIZENSHIP, IT WILL OVERLOAD THE DEMANDS UPON THE SYSTEM WHILE FURTHER INJURING THE ABILITY OF THE GOVERNMENT APPARATUS TO MEET THOSE DEMANDS.
FOR THESE REASONS IT APPEARS THE PLANNING BOARS'S RECOMMENDATIONS WILL BE FAR FROM SWEEPING AND, IF ADOPTED, WILL LIKELY DISAPPOINT MANY EXPATRIATES.
THESE PROPOSALS WILL LIKELY CALL FOR A NEW CATEGORY OF EXPATRIATES HOLDING "PERMANENT RESIDENCE CARDS".
THIS STATUS WOULD BE GRANTED ONLY TO THOSE (NOT JUST PALESTINIANS) WHO HAVE PROVEN THEIR WORTH TO THE STATE AND WHOSE SERVICES ARE LIKELY TO BE RE- QUIRED IN THE FORESEEABLE FUTURE.
IT IS NOT CLEAR WHETHER ALL EXPATRIATE NATIONALITIES WILL BE ELIGIBLE OR ONLY ARABS.
WHILE THE STAFF MEMBER DID NOT MAKE IT CLEAR WHAT BENEFITS WOULD GO WITH SUCH A STATUS, HE IMPLIED THAT IT WOULD BE NE MEANS
GUARANTEE IDENTICAL RIGHTS NOW CONFERRED UPON KUWAITIS.

MOST LIKELY SUCH STATUS COULD MEAN EQUALIZATION OF PAY FOR EQUAL WORK, THE RIGHT TO OWN REAL ESTATE AND DIRECTLY CONTROL A BUSINESS, AND OTHER MEASURES, WHEREBY SELECTED EXPATRIATES COULD IMPROVE THEIR LIVING STANDARDS HERE WITHOUT SUCCUMBING TO THE SAME SORTS OF SOCIAL ILLS WHICH HAVE OVERTAKEN MANY OF KUWAIT'S CITIZENS (E.G. SLOTH).
THE QUESTION IS STILL FAR FROM RESOLVED.
OBVIOUSLY THE FINAL VERDICT WILL REST WITH THE CROWN PRINCE/PRIME MINISTER AND THE MINISTERIAL COUNCIL.

IT NOW APPEARS LIKELY THAT THE PLANNING BOARD, WHICH IS CLOSEST THING KUWAIT HAS TO "THINK-TANK" WILL RECOMMEND AGAINST ANY WHOLESALE CHANGE OF KUWAIT'S PRESENT POLICY AND WILL COUNSEL GOK TO TRY MORE CLOSELY COORDINATE WITH OTHER ARAB GULF LITTORAL STATES TO AVOID RUINOUS SITUATION, WHEREBY EACH GOVERNMENT TRIES TO OUTDO THE OTHERS WITH POLICIES TO ATTRACT AND KEEP VALUABLE PERSONNEL.
WHETHER THIS PROGRAM, IF RECOMMENDED AND ADOPTED, WOULD BE ENOUGH TO CONTAIN THE SITUATION IS PROBLEMATIC, IT WOULD SEEM LIKELY THAT SUCH MEASURES WOULD BE SUCCESSFUL ONLY IN THE SHORT-TERM.
MCCLELLAND ']
THE LONG-DISCUSSED EASTERN BRISBANE RIVER CROSSING APPEARS TO HAVE MOVED CLOSER TO FRUTITION.
QUEENSLAND (QLD) MAIN ROADS MINISTER, RUSS HINZE, ANNOUNCED AUGUST 14 THAT TENDERS WILL BE CALLED SOON.
COST ESTIMATES FOR A BRIDGE RANGE FROM US DOLLS 60 - 70 MILLION, FOR A TUNNEL, ABOUT US DOLLS 180 MILLION (ALL 1978 DOLLARS).
A 1985 COMPLETION DATE IS ANTICIPATED.
COMPETITION, FOREIGN AND DOMESTIC, IS LIKELY TO BE BRISK AND THE QUEENSLAND GOVERNMENT WOULD PROBABLY BE MOST DISPOSED TOWARDS A JOINT VENTURE.
NO INTERNATIONAL FINANCIAL INSTITUTION PARTICIPATION IS CONTEMPLATED.
QLD. GOVERNMENT IS COMPLETING A DOLLS 200,000 DESIGN/FEASIBILITY STUDY WHICH WILL BE AVAILABLE TO POTENTIAL TENDERERS FOR A DOLLS 500 (US DOLLS 590 APPROX).
INQUIRIES SHOULD BE ADDRESSED TO: SPECIAL PROJECTS ENGINEER, MAIN ROADS DEPARTMENT, GPO BOX 1412, BRISBANE, QUEENSLAND, AUST- RALIA, 4001. 6.
QLD. GOVERNMENT IS INTERESTED IN NEGOTIATING WITH ANY ORGANIZATION WILLING TO FINANCE AND CONSTRUCT THE ENTIRE PROJECT.
THE GOVT.
WOULD BE WILLING TO GUARANTEE LOANS AND GIVE THE BUILDER/ FINANCIER TOLL RIGHTS WITH ROYALTY PAYMENTS TO THE GOVERNMENT TO BE NEGOTIATED.
IT IS EXPECTED THAT THE TOLL RIGHT PERIOD WOULD BE AROUND 30 YEARS AND THE ROYALTY PAYMENTS 10 PERCENT.
ROYALTY PAYMENTS WILL BE USED TO IMPROVE CONNECTING ROADS.
IT WOULD BE UP TO THE TENDERER TO DECIDE BETWEEN A TUNNEL OR A BRIDGE HIGH ENOUGH TO CLEAR OCEAN-GOING SHIPS.
QUALIFIED TENDERER WHICH OFFERED THE SHORTEST TOLL PERIOD AND THE HIGHEST ROYALTY RATE WOULD PROBABLY BE THE ONE SELECTED. 7.
TENDERS ARE EXPECTED TO BE LET IN OCTOBER/NOVEMBER 1978.
PRE REGISTRATION IS NOT REQUIRED, BUT INTERESTED PARTIES CAN GET THEIR NAMES ON A MAILING LIST BY WRITING TO THE ADDRESS IN PARA 5.

['1.SOUTH KOREAN AMBASSADOR TO JORDAN SANG YUNG SOH TOLD ME JANUARY 10 HE JUST PAID A "VACATION" VISIT TO SYRIA AND IRAQ.
HE HAD HAD NO TROUBLE OBTAINING VISAS TO VISIT BOTH COUNTRIES.
IN SYRIA HE SAID HE WAS EXTREMELY WELL RECEIVED BY PEOPLE, AND WAS IMPRESSED BY THE GREAT PERSONAL FRIENDLINESS TOWARD HIM AND HIS FAMILY OF ORDAINARY SYRIANS--A DEVELOPMENT HE HAD NOT ANTICIPATED.
HE SAID FURTHER THAT HE HAPPENED ON A CHANCE MEETING WITH THE BROTHER OF SYRIAN DEFENSE MINISTER, MUSTAFA TLASS IN A DAMASCUS SHOP.
THE BROTHER, A PRIVATE CONTRACTOR ABDUL KADR TLASS, INVITED AMBASSADOR SOH AND FAMILY TO A PERSONAL LUNCHEON IN A VILLAGE NEAR HOMS.

SOH INQUIRED ABOUT SYRIAN PERCEPTIONS OF SOUTH KOREA TLASS WAS SO GENUINELY INTERESTED THAT SOH ASKED HIM TO CONVEY TO HIS BROTHER SOUTH KOREA'S INTEREST IN ESTABLISHING DIPLOMATIC RELATIONS WITH SYRIA.
SOH HAS NO INDICATION OF HOW THIS APPROACH WILL BE RECEIVED BUT KNOWS OF THE CON SIDERABLE NORTH KOREAN PRESENCE IN DAMASCUS AND PYONGYANG'S CONSIDERABLE LEVERAGE.

HE ALSO TOLD ME THAT THE NORTH KOREAN AMBASSADOR IN DAMASCUS IS SEEKING DUAL ACCREDITA- TION IN AMMAN WHERE THEY HAVE AN EMBASSY AND A CHARGE, BUT THUS FAR IT HAS BEEN RESISTED IN THE THE FOREIGN MINISTRY.
PRIME MINISTER RIFAI TOLD ME THE SAE THING SOME WEEKS GAO. 3.
I N IRAQ CONDITIONS WERE MUCH DIFFERENT.
HE MET NO OFFICIALS.
PEOPLE WERE RESERVED, APPEARED HARRASSED AND GENERALLY UNFRIENDLY.
HE SAID SOUTH KOREA WOULD EVENTUALLY LIKE TO OPEN RELATIONS WITH IRAQ
ALSO BUT WS NOT BREAKING ITS NECK TO DO SO. 4.

WOULD APPRECIATE ANY COMMENT EMBASSY DAMASCUS MIGHT HAVE, ESPECIALLY ON STRENGTH OF NORTH KOREAN SYRIAN RELA TIONS AND POSSIBILITIES OF SYRIAN RECEPTIVITY TO APPROACH TO PASS ON TO AMBASSADOR SOH HERE.
PICKERING ']

MEDIATOR IN HOTEL/UNION LABOR DISPUTE RESUMED MEETINGS WITH BIU AND HEA APRIL 4 AFTER AN ABSENCE FROM THE ISLAND OF FOUR DAYS.
HE BRIEFLY INFORMED ME TODAY THAT PROGRESS IS VERY SLOW AND POSITIONS OF BOTH PARTIES SURPRISINGLY INFLEXIBLE.
IN SPITE OF THE CONTINUING DEADLOCK, IT IS EXPECTED THAT BIU PRESIDENT OTTIWELL SIMMONS WILL REFRAIN FROM CALLING A STRIKE.
THE GENERAL MEMBERSHIP VOTE AUTHORIZES, BUT DOES NOT COMPEL, A STRIKE ACTION IF NEGOTIATIONS CONTINUE UNSUCCESS- FUL THROUGH THE APRIL 9 DEADLINE.

BIU'S PRINCIPAL OPTIONS ARE TO EITHER SUMMON ANOTHER GENERAL MEMBERSHIP MEETING AND ARRANGE A VOTE FOR A NEW STRIKE DATE OR TO SIMPLY ANNOUNCE THAT, IN VIEW OF CONTINUING NEGOTIATIONS, THE STRIKE ACTION IS POSTPONED FOR THE PRESENT.

ACCEPTABLE DRAFT OF PUBLIC ANNOUNCEMENT, WHICH WOULD BE RELEASED SIMULTANEOUSLY IN WASHINGTON AND SEOUL IF ACCEPT- ABLE TO KOREA AEB FOLLOWS:
TITLE: U.S. AND SOUTH KOREA SIGN NUCLEAR INFORMATION EXCHANGE ARRANGEMENT.
FIRST PARA- GRAPH:

THE U.S. NUCLEAR REGULATORY COMMISSION AND THE KOREA ATOMIC ENERGY BUREAU TODAY SIGNED AN ARRANGEMENT PROVIDING FOR EXCHANGE OF (1) INFORMATION PERTAINING TO THE REGULA- TION OF NUCLEAR ENERGY FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE PUBLIC HEALTH AND SAFETY
AND (2) INFORMATION ON NUCLEAR SAFETY RESEARCH.
SIGNING FOR THE NUCLEAR REGULATORY COMMISSION WAS COMMIS- SIONER EDWARD A. MASON, AND FOR THE KOREA ATOMIC ENERGY BUREAU, ITS DIRECTOR BYOUNG WHIE LEE.
SECOND PARAGRAPH:

THE PURPOSE OF THIS ARRANGEMENT IS TO ENABLE THESE TWO NUCLEAR REGULATORY AGENCIES TO SHARE INFORMATION WHICH IS IMPORTANT IN THE REGULATION OF NUCLEAR ENERGY ACTIVITIES IN THE COUNTRIES, INCLUDING EARLIER ADVICE ABOUT NUCLEAR SAFETY PROBLEMS THAT MIGHT ARISE IN EITHER COUNTRY.
ALSO PROVIDED FOR IS THE SHARING OF NUCLEAR ENERGY RESEARCH INFORMATION, WHICH IS INTENDED TO REDUCE TIME AND DUPLI- CATION OF EFFORT IN THIS IMPORTANT ENDEAVOR.
THIRD PARAGRAPH:

AT THE TIME OF THE SIGNING, BOTH OFFICIALS NOTED THAT THE NEW ARRANGEMENT IS A FORMALIZATION OF THE EXCHANGE OF NUCLEAR ENERGY REGULATORY INFORMATION THAT HAS EXISTED BETWEEN THE TWO COUNTRIES FOR MANY YEARS AS PART OF A LARGER COOPERATION IN NUCLEAR ENERGY SAFETY MATTERS.
REQUEST EMBASSY IMMEDIATELY TELEGRAPH NOTIFICATION OF SIGNING OF ARRANGEMENT IN KOREA.
REQUEST EMBASSY ARRANGE FOR SIGNING CEREMONY AND PHOTOGRAPHING OF PRINCIPALS AT TIME OF SIGNING.
KISSINGER ']

CONGEN RIO IS PREPARING AIRGRAM ON CURRENT BRAZILIAN RAILROAD SITUATION, GIVEN EVALUATION OF POTENTIAL US BUSINESS OPPORTUNITIES.
RECENT ACCIDENTS EXPERIENCED BY RFFSA'S 8TH DIVISION, OPERATING COMMUTER SERVICES IN RIO, LED FEDERAL GOVERNMENT TO ALLOT 675 MILLION CRUZEIROS FOR EMERGENCY MEASURES TO RENOVATE COMMUTER SERVICE.

CONGEN OFFICER INTERVIEW WITH COL. ALUISIO WEBER, NEW SUPERINTENDENT OF 8TH DIVISION AND RECENTLY APPOINTED DIRECTOR OF RFFSA, REVEALED THAT BULK OF ALLOTTED FUNDS WILL BE USED FOR TRACK MAINTENANCE, SIGNALLING COMMUNICATIONS, TRAFFIC CONTROL AND ELECTRIC LINES OVERHAUL. 3.
ATTEMPT TO SELL FOREIGN MADE COMMUTER CARS TO RFFSA WILL MEET STRONG OPOSITION FROM DOMESTIC MANUFACTURERS.

POST BELIEVES THAT THIS OPPOSITION MAY ONLY BE OVERCOME BY OFFERING RFFSA EXTREMELY SHORT DELIVERY TERMS AND ATTRACTIVE FINANCING, OR BY OFFERING TO SUPPLY CARS ON BARTER DEAL WHEREBY NO REPEAT NO FOREIGN CURRENCY EXPENDITURES INVOLVED.
POST WELCOMES PULLMAN'S RENEWED EFFORT AND IS, OF COURSE, READY TO EXTEND APPROPRIATE ASSISTANCE AS REQUIRED.
IN RECENT TELEPHONE CONVERSATION WITH CONGEN OFFICER, MACIEL OF FERRAGENS SANTOS STATED EARLIERT DELIVERY SCHEDULE FOR COMMUTER CARS OFFERED BY PULLMAN FOR BRAZIL WAS MID-1977.
DEXTER "]
THE U.S. MILITARY PRESENCE IN GUYANA NOW CONSISTS OF TWO EXTENDED-RANGE HUEY HELICOPTERS, SEVEN UH-1 CREWMEN, AND ONE LT. COL.
SOUTHCOM LIAISON OFFICER (WHO WILL LEAVE WITHIN 48 HOURS).
THE EIGHT-MAN AIR FORCE SECURITY GUARD UNIT HAS DEPARTED FOR THE UNITED STATES.
SEVEN ELDERLY MEMBERS OF THE PEOPLE'S TEMPLE HAVE RES- ERVATIONS TO THE UNITED STATES WEDNESDAY ON A PAN AM FLIGHT TO NEW YORK.
THEY WILL BE ACCOMPANIED BY A U.S. CONSULAR OFFICER WHO WAS TEMPORARILY ASSIGNED TO GUYANA DURING THE CRISIS.
HEW, FBI AND THE SECRET SERVICE HAVE BEEN NOTIFIED AND ARE PLANNING FOR THE ARRIVAL.
THE THREE PEOPLE'S TEMPLE MEMBERS WHO ARE STILL HOSPITALIZED SEEM TO BE RE- COVERING.
IT IS STILL UNKNOWN WHEN THEY WILL BE RELEASED AND WELL ENOUGH TO TRAVEL.
THE AID DOCTOR HAS EXAMINED THEM, AND THEY HAVE BEEN VISITED SEVERAL TIMES BY A CON- SULAR OFFICER.
THE MILITARY IS READY TO EVACUATE THEM BY SPECIAL MILITARY AIRCRAFT WHEN NEEDED.
THE EMBASSY STILL HAS NO DEFINITE WORD ON THE RELEASE OF THE OTHER SURVIVORS.
DEPARTMENT TODAY RECEIVED A MAILGRAM FROM BISHOP LEROY CHINN WHO CLAIMS TO BE GENERAL OVERSEER OF THE PEOPLE'S TEMPLE MOVEMENT.
HE BLAMES THE DEATH OF CONGRESSMAN RYAN AND "THOSE PEOPLE IN GUYANA" ON RACISM OF THE U.S., NOT REVEREND JONES.
HE WARNS THAT IF THE U.S. DOES NOT STOP THE RACISM HERE, "THESE THINGS" WILL TAKE PLACE WITHIN THE U.S.
HE STATED THAT HE HAS NOTIFIED HIS AT- TORNEYS TO FILE SUIT AGAINST THE USG TO KEEP THE GOLD, CHECKS AND ALL MONEY BELONGING TO THE PEOPLE'S TEMPLE FROM "GOING BACK INTO THE U.S. TREASURY."
WE HAVE PASSED THE MAILGRAM TO L AND DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE.
THE GOG HAS FINALLY AGREED TO ALLOW THE LEGATT TO PHOTOGRAPH FINGERPRINT CARDS UNDER THE SUPERVISION OF THE IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES.
THE UNDEVELOPED FILM WILL BE SENT BACK TO THE UNITED STATES WITH THE CONSULAR OFFICER RE- TURNING TOMORROW NIGHT.
A GUYANESE MEDICAL OFFICIAL HAS AGREED TO PROVIDE DEATH CERTIFICATES ON THE BASIS OF CONFIRMED IDENTIFICATIONS FROM DOVER.
SCS HAS SENT THE FIRST LIST OF 33 NAMES TO THE EMBASSY.

RADIO BARBADOS HAS INTERVIEWED TIM CARTER, ONE OF THE SURVIVORS, AND IS REPORTING THAT, THREE DAYS BEFORE CONGRESSMAN RYAN WAS KILLED, CARTER TOLD JONES THAT HE WOULD BE KILLED BY ANTI-PEOPLE'S TEMPLE GROUPS.
RADIO BARBADOS SPECULATES THAT THE INFORMATION CONVINCED JONES TO PUT AN END TO THE PEOPLE'S TEMPLE MOVEMENT IN GUYANA.

ABE- LARDO ROSSI, ALEJANDRO ROBERTO CARIDE, FEDERICO VIDELA ESCALADA. 2.
WITH APPOINTMENT OF NEW SUPREME COURT, TOP LEVELS OF NEW GOVERNING APPARATUS ARE IN PLACE.
AN INNOVATION IS THE NINE- MEMBER LEGISLATIVE COMMITTEE HEADED BY ADMIRAL ANTONIO VANEK.
IT WILL BE REMEMBERED THAT UNDER THE 1966-73 MILITARY GOVTS NOT ONLY
CONGRESS BUT CAPITOL BUILDING ITSELF WAS CLOSED AND JUNTA, WITH ADVICE OF A FEW AIDES, PREPARED ITS OWN LEGISLATION.

AS INDICATED IN REFTEL, JUNTA REMAINS SUPREME GOVERNING BODY.
PRES IS SUBORDINATE TO JUNTA AND CAN BE REPLACED BY 2 TO 1 VOTE OF JUNTA.
WE HAVE NO FIRM INDICATION AS YET OF TIME FRAME IN WHICH JUNTA IS THINKING OF RULING.
PERONIST AND UCR CONTACTS WHO HAVE TALKED TO MILITARY, HOWEVER, SAY THEY HAVE IMPRESSION LATTER ARE THINKING ROUGHLY IN FOLLOW- ING TERMS:

SOURCES ADMIT, HOWEVER, THAT THINKING OF SUBJECT IS STILL VERY PRELIMINARY AND HOW SCENARIO IN FACT WORKS OUT WILL DEPEND VERY MUCH ON CIRCUMSTANCES AND ON HOW POLITICAL PARTIES THEMSELVES RISE TO CHALLENGE OF RE- ALIGNMENT AND PRESENTATION OF NEW IDEAS AND NEW FACES.

entities: FIRST VICE PRESIDENT ABUL GASSIM MOHAMED IBRAHIM

content: ABUL GASSIM SAID NIMEIRI'S REVOLUTION HAD ESTABLISHED AUTHORITY OF MASSES AGAINST SECTIONALISM, SECTARIANISM AND REMNANTS OF COLONIALISM.

ACCORDING TO PRESS ACCOUNTS, HE SPOKE OF RUMORS WHICH CLAIMED "ENEMIES OF REVOLUTION" ARE BUSILY FOMENTING "SIDE BATTLES" AND CALLED ON RETURNEES TO JOIN OBJECTIVE DIALOGUE ALREADY OPENED BY GOVERNMENT ON ORGANIZATION OF SUDAN SOCIALIST UNION.
ABUL GASSIM SAID "WE WANT TO KNOW EVERY POINT OF VIEW...
WE WANT TO HEAR FROM SADEQ AL MAHDI AND
HASSAN TURABI WHO ARE (NOW) MEMBERS OF POLITBURO (THEIR) POINT OF VIEW WHICH JUSTIFIED CARRYING ARMS AGAINST" MAY REVOLUTION WHICH UNIFIED PEOPLE.
ABUL GASSIM SAID SUDANGOV SECTIONAL AND SECTARIAN ACTIVITY AND "WILL STRIKE WITH AN IRON FIST ANYONE WHO TRIES TO TURN BACK" OR ENTERTAINS DOUBTS.
SUDANGOV IS CAPABLE OF PUTTING ITS ENEMIES BACK INTO PRISON.
FIRST VICE PRESIDENT SAID "CORRUPT OFFICIALS WHO HAVE SURVIVED HAVE INSULTED MAY REVOLUTION...
THERE IS NO SCOPE FOR COURTESY TO PERSON WHO DOES NOT SERVE RIGHTS OF MASSES." 3.
LOCAL OFFICIALS ALSO SPOKE IN FAVOR OF "RIGHT, JUSTICE AND PURITY."
PROCESSION WHICH STARTED FROM UNITED NATIONS SQUARE WENT TO MAIN OFFICES OF SSU TO PRESENT DOCUMENT OF SUP- PORT TO NIMEIRI, REPRESENTED BY ABUL GASSIM.

COMMENT: GENERAL OPINION IN KHARTOUM IS THAT ABUL GASSIM HIMSELF REPRESENTS MOST LIKELY THREAT TO NIMEIRI IF ANY EXISTS AND MOST LIKELY TIME FOR SUBVERSION IS DURING PERIOD THAT PRESIDENT IS OUT OF SUDAN.

DATT AGREES SECURITY WAS FACTOR IN SENIOR APPOINTMENTS BUT OUT MOST CHANGES WERE ROUTINE AND SENSIBLE FOR ADMINISTRA- TIVE REASONS.
ABUL GASSIM HAS NEVER FAVORED RECONCILIATION WITH MAHDIST LEADER SADEQ AL MAHDI OR MOSLEM BROTHERHOOD CHIEF HASSAN AL TURABI AND PROBABLY REMAINS UNFRIENDLY WITH THEM PERSONALLY.
THUS, NIMEIRI'S DEPARTURE PROVIDED OPPORTUNITY TO TALK TOUGH, WHICH PLEASED CROWD, AND TWEAK NOSES OF RETURNEES.
IF RETURNEES EXPECT TO GET POSITIONS OF INFLUENCE IN CABINET UPON PRESIDENT'S RETURN, THEY WILL HAVE TO BEAR WITH ABUL GASSIM UNTIL NIMEIRI COMES BACK. 5.

NIMEIRI WOOULD NOT HAVE MADE LENGTHY TRIP AT THIS TIME IF MUCH DOUBT EXISTED ABOUT SECURITY.
HOWEVER, SUDANESE PUBLIC IS ON EDGE, HAVING LEARNED FROM EXPERIENCE TO EXPECT TROUBLE WHEN EVERYTHING SEEMS QUIET, AND AFRAID THAT WHILE NIMEIRI IS AWAY SOMEONE MAY MOVE AGAINST HIM.

SUMMARY.

AGAINST THE BACKGROUND OF THE UNSC RENEWAL OF UNDOF AND THE IMPENDING ARRIVAL OF ISRAELI FOREIGN MINISTER ALLON IN WASHINGTON, PRAVDA'S COMMENTARY BY DEMCHENKO (DECEMBER 7) AND WEEKLY INTERNATIONAL REVIEW BY ORESTOV (DECEMBER 8) SHARPLY CRITICIZE ISRAEL AND IMPLICITLY THE U.S. FOR PROLONGING THE ME CRISIS BY DELAYING THE RECOPENING OF THE MEPC.
DEMCHENKO, GOING SOMEWHAT FURTHER THAN USUAL, IMPLIES THAT THE U.S. IS AMONG THOSE WHO ARE SABOTAGING THE CONFERENCE AND "CONDUCTING THEMSELVES LIKE OPPONENTS OF DETENTE."
END SUMMARY.
DEMCHENKO CHARGES THAT ISRAEL'S RULING CIRCLES ARE CONTINUING TO EVADE ANY CONSTRUCTION SOLUTION IN THE ME.

MOREOVER, WITH THE "SPPORT OF FOREIGN PATRONS" (USUAL SHORTHAND FOR THE U.S.), TEL AVIV IS ENGAGED IN CONTINUOUS MANEUVERING TO PROLONG THE ME CONFLICT IN ORDER TO PRESERVE ISRAEL'S OCCUPATION OF ARAB LANDS.
IMPLICITLY SUGGESTING THAT THIS SITUATION HAS A TIME LIMIT BY POINTING UP SYRIAN ASSERTIONS THAT THE UNDOF RENEWAL IS A TEMPORARY DECISION.
DEMCHENKO CALLS FOR "ENERGETIC POLITICAL MEASURES" TO ESCAPE THE DEAD END WHICH HAS BEEN CREATED IN THE ME.
AS EXPECTED DEMCHNEKO SAYS THE USSR BELIEVES THAT THE "MOST APPROPRIATE PLACE" TO DISCUSS THE ME AND TO WORK OUT A QUICK AND JUST PEACE SETTLEMENT MUST BECOME THE GENEVA CONFERENCE.

AND AFTER ASSERTING THAT THE ADVISIBILITY OF REOPENING THE MEPC'S WORK AS SOON AS POSSIBLE WAS FIXED IN THE U.S.-SOVIET COMMUNIQUE AT VLADIVOSTOK, HE CONCLUDES THAT THOSE WHO ARE "SABOTOGING" THE CONFERENCE ARE CONDUCTING THEMSELVES LIKE OPPONENTS OF DETENTE AND A STABLE PEACE IN THE ME. 3.
IN SIMILAR VEIN
THE INTERNATIONAL REVIEW CHARGES ISRAEL WITH USING ONE PRETEXT AFTER ANOTHER - ORESTOV REFERS SPECIFICALLY TO ISRAEL'S REFUSAL TO TALK TO THE POL - TO HINDER THE REOPENING OF THE MEPC.

PICKING UP KATZIR'S REMARKS ABOUT ISRAEL'S POTENTIAL NUCLEAR CAPABILITY AND RABIN'S ASSERTION THAT ISRAEL IS STRONGER NOW THAN IN 1973, ORESTOV ALSO CLAIMS THAT THE FAILURE OF ISRAEL'S "AGGRESSIVE POLICY" HAS LED TEL AVIV TO "COARSE BLACKMAIL."

HE SAYS, HOWEVER, THAT SABRE-RATTLING WILL NOT FOSTER A NORMALIZATION OF THE ME SITUATION AND CONCLUDES THAT "OBJECTIVE CONDITIONS" NOW EXIST TO RENEW THE MEPC WHICH WOULD ACHIEVE A JUST PEACE SETTLEMENT IN THE ME IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE RESOLUTIONS OF THE UN. 4.

COMMENT: WE NOTE THAT THE ABOVE COMMENT CLOSELY FOLLOWS THE LINE TAKEN BY THE SYRIAN PRESS (REFTEL A) WITH THE APPARENT DIFFERENCE THAT THE SOVIETS CONTINUE TO BE SOMEWHAT LESS DIRECT IN CRITICISM OF THE U.S. HOWEVER, FROM MOSCOW POINT OF VIEW, IT IS ALSO LIKELY THAT THE SOVIET CAMPAIGN TO PUSH GENEVA IS AIMED NOT ONLY AT ISRAEL AND THE U.S., --

THE OBVIOUS TARGETS -- BUT ALSO AT SADAT, WHOSE CONTINUING SUPPORT FOR A STEP- BY-STEP APPROACH IN THE ME, WHILE UNDER GROWING PRESSURE (REFTEL B), IS STILL A SIGNIFICANT PROBLEM FOR MOSCOW IN ITS EFFORTS TO SOLIDIFY ARAB SUPPORT FOR THE MEPC FRAMEWORK.
STOESSEL ']
